					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810#post-4367116</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810/scp-3666#post-4367116</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Sep 2019 03:12:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Nagiros</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4665703</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Heyo, finally read this after compiling the <a href="http://scp-wiki.net/esoteric-classes-complete-list">esoteric classes guide</a> a few months back. Better late than never!</p> <p>I do have to agree that the ending is a little unsatisfying. I was under the impression that this was the meddling of an outside force intent upon destroying the Veil, and to have no hint of an explanation given is… fine… under the right circumstances. This could be a nice backdrop for a discussion about the necessity of the Veil Protocol and the romanticized evil that is amnestics, and it's a shame you didn't take that route.</p> <p>One of the things that fascinates me about the Foundation is that they're wrong. By and large, humanity would stand to benefit from careful introduction of the anomalous, and exploring the extent to which mere men will go to support evil misguidedly is <em>magic</em> to me. I live for that stuff, such that I'm writing a pseudo-canon around it.</p> <p>I'm aware this article isn't new, and I'm not sure if you're even still active, but I thought I'd drop this here because your work got me thinking. Thanks!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810#post-3789626</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810/scp-3666#post-3789626</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 04 May 2018 00:42:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>SpiderPsycho</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1690393</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I feel like this SCP is more of a scenario than an actual SCP. Its sort of like propaganda that's used to justify the use of amnestics, and what would happen if they didn't use them. While I appreciate the vibe of hopelessness and utter chaos, it does break from what I sort of feel an SCP should be, contained, neutralized, or missing. It occurring in the future sort of backs up both of my other points. Still like it though, I just want some conclusion to this.</p> <p>Also yeah, how does the future stuff work? Was this something discovered by 2003?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
