					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810#post-3621054</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810/scp-3666#post-3621054</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 27 Oct 2017 18:28:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Highbinder</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3412812</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This SCP just felt ridiculous, and as others have said, way over the top. In this SCP:</p> <ul> <li>The Foundation loses it secrecy from the world</li> <li>The Foundation's entire O5 Council is killed</li> <li>International Email, calling, texting, and all social media sites are somehow eliminated</li> <li>Every single country is quarantined.</li> <li>Society itself more or less falls apart and all countries are governed by Martial Law set by The Foundation's shadow governments</li> <li>The Foundation leads a genocide against the Ethics Committee for some reason?</li> </ul> <p>In my opinion, that's just too much. A simple allergy caused the end of the world<sup>as we know it</sup>? I can't buy it. Downvoted.</p> <p>Edit: I'd also like to mention that I feel like it seems unfinished as well. You're basically leaving the world in a state of disrepair with no resolution in sight.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810#post-3613847</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810/scp-3666#post-3613847</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 15 Oct 2017 18:51:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Alten</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>702040</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's spooky magic, completely uncontainable, and effortlessly (for it's not even aware) wins at everything. Then somehow information becomes semi-publicly available for reasons and the Foundation can't do anything. Following that, the Foundation turns stupid and decides to start executing its own members because reasons.</p> <p>I dislike over the top stuff. -1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810#post-3604503</guid>
