					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810#post-3569816</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810/scp-3666#post-3569816</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 13 Aug 2017 12:24:00 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>3087025</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think this is an example of frantic attempts at containment. Like psul said above me, the cont-proc begins to go over the top to the point of illogic, but I see that as a bonus. The Foundation is backed into a corner, of course it's going to go crazy and do stupid stuff that can be counter productive.</p> <p>+1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810#post-3559314</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3097810/scp-3666#post-3559314</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 27 Jul 2017 21:58:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>psul</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2156983</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Way too over the top. Making the effect immunological, but able to resist memetics, makes no in-universe sense. Making it spread magically by proximity means there is no way it would be confined to Norway after almost a year (people from Norway do travel). I also fail to believe that the Foundation has the power to institute martial law worldwide (or do half the other things the containment procedures suggest), nor that this would be a logical approach in context. At some point the veil is blown, and executions (or shutting off global communications!) just makes things less secret, not more.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
